Customize Prediction Text

Provide custom text for variables that appear as top predictors or suggested improvements on your Salesforce records. You can have Einstein explain factors in simpler terms, such as "Repeat Purchase" instead of "Previous Closed Won Opportunity Match is True."

Custom text isn't localized to other languages and is displayed exactly as specified.

In Customize Predictions, click Customize.
During model deployment, use the customize predictions step.
For deployed models, go to Model Manager to edit the model settings for Prediction Customization.
Select a variable.
Use Suggested Improvements to customize the text shown when Einstein recommends taking an action to improve the outcome.
Configure custom text.

CUSTOMIZATION OPTION	DESCRIPTION
Don't show	No text is displayed.
Customize text	Displays the specified custom text.
Enter the custom text.
For variables with text values, define custom text for individual values.
For variables with numeric values, define custom text for suggested changes to the value.
You can include placeholders inside the custom text.

PLACEHOLDER	DESCRIPTION
[field_name]	Variable name.
[value]	Suggested value or range.
[diff]	Difference between the current value and the suggested value or range.
[value_high]
[value_low]
[max_diff]
[min_diff]	
Top of the suggested range.
Bottom of the suggested range.
Difference between [value_high] and the current value.
Difference between [value_low] and the current value.

Optionally, click Add Value to customize text for another value in the variable. Click Save.

Recommendations from Einstein that use labels from the dataset can be difficult to understand. Customizing the text Einstein displays can make it easier to understand.
title: Customizing Prediction Text in Einstein Discovery
